---
import TextAndImage from "../components/TextAndImage.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import WhatIsConf from "../img/WhatIsConf.png";
import WhoAttends from "../img/WhoAttends.png";
import SmallMeeting from "../img/SmallMeeting.png";
import LargeMeeting from "../img/LargeMeeting.png";
import WorkHardPlayHard from "../img/WorkHardPlayHard.png";
---

<BaseLayout
    pageTitle="About The Matrix Conference"
    description="The Matrix Conference is organised by The Matrix Foundation and its sponsors. Several tracks spread across several days to discuss topics ranging from how Matrix powers the public sector to how encryption works."
>
    <section id="what-is-conf">
        <TextAndImage imgSrc={WhatIsConf}>
            <h2>What is The Matrix Conference</h2>
            <p>
                Run by The Matrix Foundation, the Conference brings together all
                parts of the Matrix universe.
            </p>
            <p>
                We deliberately mix all types of Matrix users, developers and
                enthusiasts so that a whole bunch of people that use Matrix in
                different ways can learn from one another.
            </p>
            <p>
                Meet people just like you, and meet people who are very
                different to you!
            </p>
        </TextAndImage>
    </section>
    <section id="who-attends">
        <TextAndImage imgSrc={WhoAttends} reverse>
            <h2>Who attends #MatrixConf?</h2>
            <p>
                More than 300 people attended The Matrix Conference 2025 in
                Strasbourg (we were totally sold out!).
            </p>

            <p>
                Around a third of those attending were running Matrix-based
                deployments in public sector organisations or other large
                workplaces.
            </p>

            <p>
                Another third were from organisations offering Matrix-based
                products and services.
            </p>

            <p>
                And the other third are developers, hackers, academics and
                digital rights activists.
            </p>
        </TextAndImage>
    </section>
    <section id="large-end-user-orgs">
        <TextAndImage imgSrc={SmallMeeting}>
            <h2>Why large end-user organisations attend</h2>
            <p>
                The Matrix Conference is the best place to learn more about
                Matrix. Hear directly from Matthew Hodgson and Amandine Le Pape,
                Matrix co-founders.
            </p>
            <p>
                See how governments, public sector sector organisations and
                other workplaces are transforming the way they work using Matrix.
            </p>
            <p>Learn how service providers deploy Matrix for workplace use.</p>
        </TextAndImage>
    </section>
    <section id="academics-communities">
        <TextAndImage imgSrc={LargeMeeting} reverse>
            <h2>Why academics, communities and hackers attend</h2>
            <p>
                This is the place to meet your community, users, and
                contributors. Come solve problems you couldn’t solve online, and
                learn about the next big thing in the Matrix ecosystem.
            </p>
            <p>
                Get in touch and speak directly to the experts driving
                the development of the technology, including the Spec Core Team,
                the people working bringing MLS to Matrix,
                the developers behind MatrixRTC,
                and creators of Trust and Safety and community management tooling.
            </p>
        </TextAndImage>
    </section>
    <section id="work-play-hard">
        <TextAndImage imgSrc={WorkHardPlayHard}>
            <h2>Work hard, play hard!</h2>
            <p>
                During the day, #MatrixConf offers a <a href="/schedule/"
                    >packed and varied agenda</a
                >.
            </p>

            <p>
                Pick and choose from simultaneous sessions to suit your
                interests, from delivering on service levels agreement to
                geeking out.
            </p>

            <p>
                Your brain will be bursting with ideas by the end of each day!
            </p>

            <p>
                Come the evening, hang out with other Matrix enthusiasts in more
                casual environments and enjoy the warm Autumnal evenings in
                beautiful Malmö! See <a href="/facts/#getting-there"
                    >where the venue is</a
                >.
            </p>
        </TextAndImage>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
